race.comment: They'll go like the clappers in this. FLYING AURELIUS (6) showed plenty of potential winning his first three career outings before just missing the frame at the past couple. Has been very heavily supported in all five outings to date and where there's smoke there's fire. Will prove hard to toss. BLUE SPINEL (3) is a three-time winner here on her home circuit and gets the deadly Gollan/Maloney combination. Right in this contest from the favourable draw. The well-related HEESEN (9) (half to 2xG3 winner California Zimbol) is one from one over this course and distance and gets 3kg off with the claim. Top-three credentials. SIRKEL (14) is usually thereabouts and looks one for the multiples.
